<BaseLayout title="Questions and answers | LetsFixIndia" description="How to read, verify, and improve the LetsFixIndia public record.">
  <div class="page-shell"><header class="record-header"><p class="eyebrow">Questions and answers</p><h1>How to use the record well.</h1><p class="lede">The source links matter as much as the summaries. Here is how to read them responsibly.</p></header>
    <div class="method-grid section"><article class="method-card"><h3>Is this a verdict?</h3><p>No. It is a source-led record. Allegations, reporting, court findings, and final outcomes are kept distinct.</p></article><article class="method-card"><h3>What does a source label mean?</h3><p>Linked sources can be opened now. Pending labels show work still needed in the public source ledger.</p></article><article class="method-card"><h3>What if something is wrong?</h3><p>Send the precise correction and the strongest supporting source. Dates, numbers, legal outcomes, and wording all matter.</p><a class="read-record" href="/submit">Send a correction →</a></article><article class="method-card"><h3>How can I help?</h3><p>Read closely, share the source with the claim, and contribute evidence that makes an entry more accurate.</p></article></div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
